# Refs

How git names a commit. Every commit-ish accepted by @git/branch, @git/rebase,
@git/cherry, @git/bisect, and @git/history is built from this grammar.

## Symbolic refs

| Ref | Points at |
|-----|-----------|
| `HEAD` | the current checkout (tip of the current branch) |
| `@` | shorthand for `HEAD` |
| `<branch>` / `<tag>` | the commit a branch or tag names |
| `origin/<branch>` | the remote-tracking copy of a branch |
| `FETCH_HEAD` / `MERGE_HEAD` | last fetched / merging-in commit |
| `ORIG_HEAD` | HEAD before the last big move (reset, rebase, merge) |

## Ancestry â€” walk backward from a ref

`~` follows first parents; `^` selects which parent at a merge.

| Form | Means |
|------|-------|
| `HEAD~` / `HEAD~1` | first parent (one commit back) |
| `HEAD~3` | three first-parent steps back |
| `HEAD^` | first parent (same as `~1`) |
| `HEAD^2` | the *second* parent of a merge commit |
| `HEAD^@` | all parents of HEAD |

## Ranges â€” for log and diff

| Form | Selects |
|------|---------|
| `A..B` | commits reachable from `B` but not `A` (what `B` adds) |
| `A...B` | commits on either side but not both (symmetric difference) |
| `^A B` | reachable from `B`, excluding `A` (same as `A..B`) |
| `B --not A` | the explicit form of exclusion |

`main..HEAD` is "my unmerged work"; `main...HEAD` in a log shows both branches'
divergence. Feed these straight to @git/history.

## Reflog and date selectors â€” `@{...}`

The per-ref history of where a ref pointed. Recovery leans on this (@git/recover).

| Form | Means |
|------|-------|
| `HEAD@{2}` | where HEAD was two moves ago |
| `<branch>@{1}` | the branch's previous position |
| `HEAD@{yesterday}` | where HEAD pointed at that time |
| `<branch>@{upstream}` (`@{u}`) | the branch's tracked remote ref |
| `stash@{0}` | the newest @git/stash entry |

## Refspecs â€” `src:dst`

The `+src:dst` form used by fetch/push to map one ref onto another.

| Refspec | Does |
|---------|------|
| `main:main` | push local `main` to remote `main` |
| `HEAD:refs/heads/feature` | push current commit to a named remote branch |
| `+refs/heads/*:refs/remotes/origin/*` | fetch all branches; `+` allows non-fast-forward |
| `:topic` | empty source = delete remote `topic` |
